Ukraine Update: Zelenskiy Says 40,000 Evacuated, Attacks Persist
Video player cover image
WATCH: Surrender is “not acceptable to us,” says Ukrainian Foreign Minister Dmytro Kuleba, following talks with Russian counterpart Sergei Lavrov. Source: Bloomberg
Bloomberg News
March 10, 2022, 7:46 AM UTC Updated on March 10, 2022, 10:46 PM UTC
Share this article
Copied

Sign up here to get the latest updates on the Russian invasion of Ukraine. You can also follow us on Telegram here .

About 40,000 civilians were able to leave combat zones on Thursday, Ukraine’s President Volodymyr Zelenskiy said in a video address. He said Russian attacks are preventing evacuations from southern cities including Mariupol.
